News gets out that Radia defeated Doppler and saved Alderman Hayes. When some crooks contemplate what it means for some C.O.W.L. members to be back on the prowl, they are attacked by a mysterious, vicious vigilante (Sparrow) who tells them to confess to the police about what they saw when John Pierce was killed.

Radia heals in the hospital after her encounter with Doppler. Geoffrey Warner confronts her for breaking the strike, but she doesn't care. He threatens her by saying her can give someone else the Radia costume and name. Outside he papers over their argument by saying that it was his idea for her to stop Doppler.

Warner meets with mobster Camden Stone later. He wants Radia dead for what she did, and Warner, his ethics becoming more and more compromised, reluctantly agrees.

Evelyn continues her search for proof about John's murder without success, or support from her department.

Blaze confronts Eclipse about the fire at city hall, which was caused by an unknown hero during a scuffle on the picket line. Blaze thinks Frank did it, and wants Eclipse to say he saw him do it. He tries to blackmail Eclipse with information about what he and Radia have been doing to Stone's men outside of the strike. Eclipse walks out, using his powers to mess with Blaze's power glove, but he's scared.

Two more costumed villains rob a pharmacy, but are interrupted by the cops. They kill two police officers in their escape, breaking the rules that Warner's rule with Stone about no killing.

One of the criminals intimidated by Sparrow turns himself in to Evelyn and tells her the truth about how Arclight murdered John Pierce.

The stars of the hit [adult swim] show continue their first epic comic book adventure in Part Two of "The Wubba Lubba Dub Dub of Wall Street"! Trapped in a winding labyrinth of Rick's own design, Morty desperately searches for an escape as Rick desperately searches for his hidden cache of booze. Meanwhile, the rest of the family tries to figure out what to do with Morty's now-vacant room, not to mention the weird alien Jerry accidentally released from Rick's lab.

Synopsis

Wubba Lubba Dub Dub of Wall Street, Part Two

In Space Court, Rick fails to entice the judges with Morty's scantily-clad body. The court finds Rick and Morty guilty of numerous crimes and sentences them to life in the Clackspire Labyrinth. The two are transported and unceremoniously dropped into the labyrinth and are immediately attached by a water alien. Rick and Morty run.

Back home, Jerry is banished to the basement (or, as he calls it: "Jerryworld") because of his decision to have Rick and Morty arrested. Jerry knocks over some of Rick's things and a crawly alien-thing escapes to the upstairs where Beth and Summer argue over what to do with Morty's now vacant room.

In the Clackspire Labyrinth, Morty is physically and mentally exhausted. He is surprised to see Rick changed into some fresh clothes and with a bottle of booze. Rick explains that he built the labyrinth - "Clackspire" is an anagram for "Rick's Place". Rick finds Morty some new clothes in a hidden panel - one of several he planted when he built the place - and the two wander around for a while looking for a way out. Rick begins to wax morose and Morty notes that Rick is drinking too much. It's all prep for Rick to find a portal home and push Morty through. There had only been enough power for one person, so Rick remains in the labyrinth alone while Morty makes it home.

Summer Spectacular, Part Two

During a job interview, Summer reflects upon a time when she led a food revolution. The interviewer asks her to elaborate on her statement that she "technically" has food leadership and management. Summer declines.

Note: Mr. Poopybutthole only appears on a variant cover.
